Wow. another place I haven't given a review for!!

Calera package store and I go way back.  Well, not really...but I popped into this location BEFORE I decided to move here.  We were scouting the area and I was intrigued by the idea of a wine boutique.  There was nothing like that available in Calera.  Shocker, right??  Any who, moving on....

Calera package store offers a variety of wines that you may or may not find in grocery stores. Today I bought two wines for my girl friend.  She walked in and they were sitting there waiting for her.  I recently bought a wine captain (not a fridge...totally different) and I need to fill it with wines that I can save and wine that I can drink. I bought one wine that she can keep for years and I bought another that she could save but lets be honest...she probably won't.
Good selection...great customer service and perfect for what I'm looking for to feed my  new found love of collecting wines!

The machine appeared to have an overlay that had been mounted to the credit card machine. When I looked up, the cashier looked away quickly and would not make eye contact.

The following day, July 18, I began to see fraudulent charges posting to my bank account. I reported the charges to regions and was told by the bank manager that it appeared that someone had cloned my debit card. Regions is opening an investigation into the fraud.

TO THE OWNER OF THIS STORE-
YOUR EMPLOYEE (white female with brown hair, approx late 30s to 40s) that was working the register on July 17, 2018 around 1pm is a thief!!
If she stole from me, she'll steal from you and the rest of your customers!!

name: Katheryn Young
text:
A Cup of Everything Convenience Store is truly convenient--a menu loaded with coffees, teas, and sandwiches primarily; and a medium-sized cache of snack bars, bottled and canned drinks, chips, and even things like headache medicine, this little restaurant/shop is a wonderful addition to the Square in downtown HSV. In addition to having just about anything you might find yourself needing while out on a stroll around downtown, or serving jury duty, etc., the staff is incredibly friendly and will (in my experience) go out of their way to ensure your good day.
However, you will be paying convenience store prices for most of their selections: a cup of coffee will only leave you a little better off than a visit to Starbucks (without the carefully constructed flavor--ACoE's coffee has been particularly bitter in my experience, even with sugar and cream), and the food can get a little pricey as well. Packaged foods, on the other hand, seem to be a bit cheaper than, say, the store inside the courthouse but it's not really enough to keep me from driving the little extra distance to the Publix at Twickenham Square.
The cozy atmosphere and neat meeting space upstairs, though, may be enough to counter-balance the slightly higher prices and not-so-awesome coffee--and a warm Spring day sat outside with a cold cup of iced tea and a fresh-made sandwich can't quite be beat.
So all-in-all, if you don't mind spending a bit more and not getting Starbucks-quality coffee, you will get a cozy, unique atmosphere great for a refreshing time on your own or with friends.

resp.text:
Mallory,

I'm very sorry our staff made you feel unwelcome.  There is absolutely no excuse for that.  We are open for business right up until our posted hours say we close and you are always welcome.  I personally instruct staff to NEVER "last call" our customers.  Has this occurred more than once?  I would appreciate further information on this issue if you don't mind.  Could you email me at info@wishyouwerebeer.net with the night you visited so that I can address the problem with my staff?  I would certainly appreciate it.

I would like to address a couple other issues you mentioned though.  The only time prices would increase is when a particular product price is raised from wholesaler to us.  We do not simply raise prices arbitrarily on everything in house.  I would be happy to look into something in particular if you care to let me know.

The other issue is with the former Madison store, which is not "gone" per se.  We sold that store to another couple and they decided to change the name of the business to Madison Taproom.  It still exists, but under new ownership and name now.  It is important to me to make that distinction between selling a business and simply going out of business (which did not happen).

Your business is very important to us.  I gather from your comments that you have been a customer of ours in the past and I would love to keep that relationship strong.  Please contact me so that I can help make things right.  Thank you.

Damon Eubanks, Owner (WYWB)

I am also disappointed, Andrew, because I know you and you know me, and you have been to both of my businesses on several occasions.  Therefore, I consider YOU a regular and I definitely appreciate your business more than words can say.  You have never written a negative review of either of our stores in the past that I am aware of, so this one is particularly troubling. I have to wonder if all of your experiences have been this bad.  I certainly hope not!

I was there at the store last night and did see you briefly as I was helping set up our food vendor outside.  I was not aware you were having so much trouble with my staff over at the bar. I wish you had said something to me directly so that I could have made a correction on the spot.  As unfortunate as this review is,  I still appreciate your time and feedback.  I will address your issues with my staff today and make necessary corrections to make sure this does not happen again. Definitely one of the best stores in North Alabama to beer shop at. Extensive selection both on tap and bottled/canned. A good go to for liquor if the ABC store is closed.

The staff can be hit or miss sometimes but almost all of my interactions and transactions here have been pleasant. Most of them will have really good recommendations if you just ask.

The hit or miss about the staff has to do with pricing. Three out of the last five times I've been in there a product rings up more at the register than what's indicated on the pricing sticker (both on the shelf and attached to the product itself). Once I found a single product with three different prices on the bottles. When brought to the staff's attention they've acted put out that I called them on the pricing issue.
